---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import stats from '../data/stats.json';

const t = stats.totals;
const fmt = (v: number | null | undefined, dp = 0) =>
  v == null ? 'n/a' : v.toLocaleString('en-GB', { minimumFractionDigits: dp, maximumFractionDigits: dp });
const months = [...stats.monthly].reverse();
const monthName = (m: string) =>
  new Date(m + '-15T12:00:00Z').toLocaleDateString('en-GB', { month: 'long', year: 'numeric' });
const ukDate = (iso: string) =>
  new Date(iso + 'T12:00:00Z').toLocaleDateString('en-GB', { day: 'numeric', month: 'short', year: 'numeric' });
const range = stats.meta.first_date && stats.meta.last_date
  ? `${ukDate(stats.meta.first_date)} → ${ukDate(stats.meta.last_date)}`
  : '';

const datasetJsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Dataset',
  name: 'Solar by Numbers: daily UK solar & battery performance data',
  description:
    'Daily measured performance of a 10.45 kWp (22× Aiko 475W) UK solar array with a 15.06 kWh SigenStor battery and Sigenergy EC 8.0 SP inverter on Octopus Agile: PV generation, grid import and export, house consumption, battery charge/discharge, daily cost and savings versus a no-solar baseline. Published automatically every night from Home Assistant and Predbat. Location: Hampshire, UK. East/west roof.',
  url: 'https://solarbynumbers.co.uk/stats/',
  license: 'https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/',
  isAccessibleForFree: true,
  creator: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'Solar by Numbers', url: 'https://solarbynumbers.co.uk/' },
  temporalCoverage: stats.meta.first_date && stats.meta.last_date
    ? `${stats.meta.first_date}/${stats.meta.last_date}`
    : undefined,
  spatialCoverage: { '@type': 'Place', name: 'Hampshire, United Kingdom' },
  variableMeasured: [
    'PV generation (kWh)', 'Grid import (kWh)', 'Grid export (kWh)',
    'House consumption (kWh)', 'Battery charge (kWh)', 'Battery discharge (kWh)',
    'Daily net cost (GBP)', 'Daily saving vs no-solar baseline (GBP)',
  ],
  measurementTechnique: 'Sigenergy inverter energy meters and Predbat daily cost tracking, exported via Home Assistant',
  distribution: [
    {
      '@type': 'DataDownload',
      encodingFormat: 'application/rss+xml',
      contentUrl: 'https://solarbynumbers.co.uk/rss.xml',
    },
  ],
};
---

<Base title="Live performance stats" description="Real daily solar generation, grid import and export, battery throughput and payback progress, published automatically every night from Home Assistant." jsonLd={datasetJsonLd}>
  <section class="reveal">
    <p class="kicker">{t.days} days of data · {range} {stats.meta.sample && <span class="badge-sample">demo data</span>}</p>
    <h1>The numbers</h1>
    <p style="max-width:46rem">
      Every figure below is pushed automatically from Home Assistant at 00:15 each night. The kWh
      come from the Sigenergy inverter's own meters and the costs from Predbat's daily tracking,
      including its estimate of what each day would have cost with no solar or battery. None of it
      is typed in by hand. <a href="/stack/#pipeline">How the pipeline works →</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="reveal" style="margin-top:2.2rem">
    <div class="panel ticks">
      <p class="kicker" style="margin-bottom:1.2rem">Running totals</p>
      <div class="grid-4">
        <div class="stat gen">
          <span class="stat-label">Generated</span>
          <span class="stat-value">{fmt(t.pv_generation)}<span class="unit">kWh</span></span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat exp">
          <span class="stat-label">Exported</span>
          <span class="stat-value">{fmt(t.grid_export)}<span class="unit">kWh</span></span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat imp">
          <span class="stat-label">Imported</span>
          <span class="stat-value">{fmt(t.grid_import)}<span class="unit">kWh</span></span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="stat-label">Saved</span>
          <span class="stat-value">£{fmt(t.savings)}</span>
          <span class="stat-sub">{((stats.meta.payback_progress ?? 0) * 100).toFixed(1)}% of £{fmt(stats.meta.system_cost_gbp)}</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {(t.unpaid_export_kwh ?? 0) > 0.05 && (
    <section class="reveal" style="margin-top:1.2rem">
      <div class="panel" style="border-left:4px solid var(--import)">
        <div style="display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; align-items:baseline; gap:0.6rem 2rem">
          <div class="stat imp">
            <span class="stat-label">Given away unpaid</span>
            <span class="stat-value">£{fmt(t.foregone_export_gbp, 2)}</span>
            <span class="stat-sub">{fmt(t.unpaid_export_kwh, 1)} kWh exported for free</span>
          </div>
          <p class="muted" style="max-width:36rem; margin:0">
            Until the final installation certification comes through we earn nothing for export,
            but the inverter still pushes surplus to the grid once the battery is full. This is
            what that donated energy would have earned at the 12p rate.
            <a href="/tariff/">The certification story →</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  )}

  <section class="chart-panel panel reveal">
    <p class="chart-title">Daily generation vs consumption</p>
    <canvas id="chart-energy" height="120"></canvas>
  </section>

  <section class="chart-panel panel reveal">
    <p class="chart-title">Grid flows · export ↑ / import ↓</p>
    <canvas id="chart-grid" height="120"></canvas>
  </section>

  <section class="chart-panel panel reveal">
    <p class="chart-title">Battery throughput · charged ↑ / discharged ↓</p>
    <canvas id="chart-battery" height="120"></canvas>
  </section>

  <section class="chart-panel panel reveal">
    <p class="chart-title">Daily net cost vs no-solar baseline</p>
    <canvas id="chart-cost" height="120"></canvas>
  </section>

  <section class="chart-panel panel reveal">
    <p class="chart-title">Cumulative savings → £{fmt(stats.meta.system_cost_gbp)} payback</p>
    <canvas id="chart-payback" height="120"></canvas>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-top:3rem">
    <h2>Monthly ledger</h2>
    <div class="table-scroll">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Month</th>
          <th class="num">Days</th>
          <th class="num">Gen kWh</th>
          <th class="num">Export kWh</th>
          <th class="num">Import kWh</th>
          <th class="num">Net cost £</th>
          <th class="num">Axle £</th>
          <th class="num">Saved £</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {months.map((m) => (
          <tr>
            <td>{monthName(m.month)}</td>
            <td class="num">{m.days}</td>
            <td class="num">{fmt(m.pv_generation, 1)}</td>
            <td class="num">{fmt(m.grid_export, 1)}</td>
            <td class="num">{fmt(m.grid_import, 1)}</td>
            <td class="num">{fmt(m.net_cost, 2)}</td>
            <td class="num axle-cell">{m.axle_earnings ? `£${fmt(m.axle_earnings, 2)}` : '—'}</td>
            <td class="num" style="color:var(--export)">{fmt(m.savings, 2)}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
        <tr class="total">
          <td>All time</td>
          <td class="num">{t.days}</td>
          <td class="num">{fmt(t.pv_generation, 1)}</td>
          <td class="num">{fmt(t.grid_export, 1)}</td>
          <td class="num">{fmt(t.grid_import, 1)}</td>
          <td class="num">{fmt(t.net_cost, 2)}</td>
          <td class="num axle-cell">{t.axle_earnings ? `£${fmt(t.axle_earnings, 2)}` : '—'}</td>
          <td class="num">{fmt(t.savings, 2)}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    </div>
    <p class="muted">A day's saving comes from Predbat's no-solar comparison: what the day's
    usage would have cost if it were all imported at the actual half-hourly Agile rates, minus
    what it actually cost. Predbat also credits energy banked into the battery during the day
    (priced at the rate it later displaces), and debits energy drawn down, so a day that fills the
    battery scores higher than a pure avoided-import view. Over a run of days the battery starts
    and ends at a similar charge and it evens out. Standing charges hit both sides equally, so
    they cancel.</p>
    <p class="muted"><strong>Axle £</strong> is the VPP grid-event income (battery exported at £1/kWh
    during demand events), measured from our own meter. It is <em>already part of</em> the Saved
    figure — Predbat prices the event export into the day's net cost — so it counts toward payback
    too; the column just breaks out how much of the saving came from VPP events. Don't add it to
    Saved.</p>
  </section>

  <style>
    .axle-cell { color: #e8472b; font-weight: 600; }
  </style>

  <script src="../scripts/charts.js"></script>
</Base>
